        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">France to Lebanon</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-oct-25-2.jpg" alt="France to Lebanon" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">At a Paris conference, international partners pledged <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20241024-key-figures-absent-as-france-hosts-lebanon-aid-conference-in-paris" target="_blank">$1 billion in aid</a> to Lebanon. The pledge includes $800 million for humanitarian assistance to aid displaced and vulnerable populations affected by regional conflicts, especially amid escalating violence between Hezbollah and Israel. Another $200 million is set aside to strengthen Lebanon’s armed forces, especially for security needs in southern Lebanon.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cvgx3zjvjg3o" target="_blank">ongoing conflict in Lebanon</a> has caused widespread family displacement and impacted the country's fragile economy. French President Emmanuel Macron highlighted the need for significant aid to assist the Lebanese people during this crisis. The conference also discussed plans to strengthen Lebanon's military resources, particularly for potential deployments in the southern region.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
