          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇭🇺 Hungary:</strong> Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán accused the EU of attempting to install a “<a href="https://apnews.com/article/hungary-orban-eu-government-speech-d9d73c58566a6a3fbafaa77f4d702bec" target="_blank">puppet government</a>” in Hungary, comparing the situation to the <a href="https://abouthungary.hu/blog/remembering-1956-soviet-type-oppression-then-and-now" target="_blank">Soviet oppression of 1956</a>. Speaking on the anniversary of the Hungarian uprising against Soviet rule, Orbán urged citizens to resist EU influence, criticizing Brussels and Ukraine’s President Zelenskyy for seeking to extend the war in Ukraine. Orbán faces increasing political pressure as opposition leader Peter Magyár of the <a href="https://tvpworld.com/83125481/hungarian-main-opposition-party-surpasses-pm-orbans-fidesz-in-second-poll" target="_blank">Tisza party gains support</a>, overtaking Orbán’s Fidesz in the polls for the first time since 2010.</p>
